            <ArticleTitle>On the transition to secondary Kerr combs in whispering-gallery mode resonators.</ArticleTitle>
            <Pagination>
                <MedlinePgn>3078-3081</MedlinePgn>
            </Pagination>
            <ELocationID EIdType="doi" ValidYN="Y">10.1364/OL.44.003078</ELocationID>
            <Abstract>
                <AbstractText>We demonstrate that extended dissipative structures in Kerr-nonlinear whispering-gallery mode resonators undergo a spatiotemporal instability, as the pumping parameters are varied. We show that the dynamics of the patterns beyond this bifurcation yield specific Kerr comb and sub-comb spectra that can be subjected to a phase of frequency-locking when optimal conditions are met. Our numerical results are found to be in agreement with experimental measurements.</AbstractText>
            </Abstract>
